1. For Any Python Project Create Seprate environment Using - python -m menv environment_name
2. For Installing FastApi You Have To Write - Pip Install FastApi
3. And For Fast Api Uvicorn Is Also Needed Which Works As a server - pip install uvicorn

Main Programming 
    1. For FastApi Works First You Have To Create On Main Python File Then In That ( From fastapi import FastAPI ) And Create A Proper Object Or Instance Of Fast FastAPI
       Like App = FastApi () 
       So When We Need To Use FastApi Just Call App Okayy
    
    2. So Basic Second Step Is That You Have To Create API ( Routes )
       So It's Look Like :-
            @app.get("/"):
            def function_name():
                // All Your Logical Parts Here And After That
                return {"Message":"Hello Ratikant"}

    3. So As You Know Their Any Many Types Of Routes Or Api's Like
        1.Get 2.Post 3.Put 4.Patch 5.Update 6.Delete 
        So Depending upon Your Requirements You Can Create Routs Types

    4. To Run Our FastApi Program You Have To Write A Command 
        - uvicorn main:app --reload // This is main Command To Run The Project 
        - But You Can Use It also ( uvicorn main:app ) But Problem Is That If You Do Chances In You Program Then You Have to again execute this command to 
          see the changes .
        - But Using uvicorn main:app --reload helps that if you make changes in code and refresh in web then you will see the changes you dont have to be 
          execute this command again and again . 

    5. Their Are Two Types Of Parameter In FastApi 
        - 1. Path Parameter
            - In This We Send Values Using Url And In Paramter Column We Have To Mention Its Datatype
                @app.get("/Path-Parameter/{parameter}") # Here You Can Take Any Name You Want
                def path_parameter(parameter:str):      # Here We Have To Declare Our Datatype Of Parameter
                    // Code Goes Here
        
        - 2. Query Parameter
            - In This We Send Values By Body To Hide From Url and we can send multiple values using Query Parameter
                @app.get("/query-parameter")
                def query_parameter(parameter1:dataype , parameter2:dataype):
                    // Code Goes Here

            - But If You Want Something Optional Or Cant Decide User Will Fill This or not then you should use optional Keyword
            - For That You Have To Import ( from typing import Optional )
            - You Can Do Optional Any Parameter As You Want 
                @app.get("query-optional-parameter")
                def query_optional_parameter(parameter1: Optional[datatype]=None , parameter2:dataype)
                    // Code Goes Here